        GenerationLease activeLease = registry.active();
        DispatchBinding binding = ACTIVE.get();
        if (binding == null) {
            DispatchBinding created = new DispatchBinding(activeLease);
            ACTIVE.set(created);
            return created;
        }

        if (!binding.matches(activeLease)) {
            DispatchBinding replacement = new DispatchBinding(activeLease);
            ACTIVE.set(replacement);
            return replacement;
        }

        return binding;
    }
```

When `binding.matches(activeLease)` is false, it creates a `replacement` and sets it to the `ThreadLocal`. However, it **never closes the old `binding`**. 

Let's check `DispatchBinding.java` to see what its `close()` method does. It likely releases the lease. If it's not called, the old lease's reference count will never reach zero, so the generation will never be closed, and the ClassLoader will leak.
Plan: 1. Examine `src/main/java/io/harbor/textd/core/DispatchBinding.java`.
2. Verify if `DispatchBinding.close()` releases the lease.
3. Fix `WorkerBindings.java` to close the old binding when replacing it.

